Here's a complete implementation:

### XAML

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             xmlns:models="clr-namespace:MyApp.Models"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ItemsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ItemsViewModel">

    <RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
                 Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">

        <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                        SelectionMode="Single"
                        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                        SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">

            <CollectionView.ItemsLayout>
                <LinearItemsLayout Orientation="Vertical"
                                   ItemSizingStrategy="MeasureFirstItem" />
            </CollectionView.ItemsLayout>

            <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
                <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                    <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                        <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                               WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                        <VerticalStackLayout Grid.Column="1" VerticalOptions="Center">
                            <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                            <Label Text="{Binding Description}"
                                   FontSize="12" TextColor="Gray" />
                        </VerticalStackLayout>
                    </Grid>
                </DataTemplate>
            </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>

            <CollectionView.EmptyView>
                <ContentView>
                    <Label Text="No items found."
                           HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </ContentView>
            </CollectionView.EmptyView>

        </CollectionView>
    </RefreshView>
</ContentPage>
```

### ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> _items = [];

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? _selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    public ItemsViewModel(IApiService api)
    {
        _api = api;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        var navParam = new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", SelectedItem }
        };

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("details", navParam);

        // Clear selection so the user can re-select the same item
        SelectedItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items.Clear();
                foreach (var item in data)
                    Items.Add(item);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // Stops the spinner
        }
    }
}
```

### Key bindings explained

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool IsRefreshing` | Controls the refresh spinner; **must be set to `false`** when done |
| `Command` (RefreshView) | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh gesture |
| `SelectedItem` | `Item? SelectedItem` | Two-way binding tracks the currently selected item |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires when selection changes — triggers navigation |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Use `ObservableCollection`, not `List`, so adds/removes update the UI automatically |

### Important details

- **Reset `SelectedItem` to `null`** after navigating — otherwise the same item can't be re-selected.
- **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block so the spinner always stops, even on errors.
- **Update the collection on the UI thread** via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
- **Never use `ViewCell`** in the template — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, or any `View` directly.
- `MeasureFirstItem` on `LinearItemsLayout` improves scroll performance for uniform rows.
